WEBVTT

00:02.769 --> 00:03.802
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.837 --> 00:05.371
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.908 --> 00:10.776
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:12.112 --> 00:14.079
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:14.114 --> 00:16.715
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:16.750 --> 00:18.650
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:18.685 --> 00:23.088
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:25.177 --> 00:27.412
[ Militaristic music plays ]

00:30.015 --> 00:32.116
[ Humming ]

00:35.788 --> 00:37.455
[ Humming stops ]

00:40.025 --> 00:42.059
[ Humming resumes ]

00:42.094 --> 00:44.862
Good morning, Kimby.
Working hard or hardly working?

00:44.897 --> 00:45.863
[ Chuckles, slurps ]

00:45.898 --> 00:46.931
Clarence!

00:46.966 --> 00:48.833
[ Slurping ]

00:48.868 --> 00:50.067
Lips off the faucet, boy.

00:50.102 --> 00:52.203
Oh, sorry, Mr. Reese.

00:52.238 --> 00:53.337
'S okay.

00:53.372 --> 00:54.371
-[ Panting ]
-Hey!

00:54.406 --> 00:56.173
Randell!
No runnin' in the halls!

00:56.208 --> 00:58.609
[ Chomping ]

00:58.644 --> 01:02.012
Belson, there is no gum
in Aberdale Elementary!

01:02.047 --> 01:03.848
[ Pop! ]

01:03.883 --> 01:05.516
Noles.
Spit it out, boy.

01:05.551 --> 01:07.418
[ Chomping ]

01:07.453 --> 01:08.919
'Kay.

01:08.954 --> 01:10.521
[ Spits ]

01:10.556 --> 01:11.956
[ Groans ]

01:11.991 --> 01:15.393
Belson, get back here
and put that in the trash!

01:19.999 --> 01:23.033
[ Grunting ]

01:23.068 --> 01:26.537
Melanie: So, that covers
math skills,

01:26.572 --> 01:28.272
but I was hoping to add...
Okay, over here --

01:28.307 --> 01:29.573
Oh, uh, Melanie.
Brenda.

01:29.608 --> 01:31.575
A little midday
lesson plannin', hmm?

01:31.610 --> 01:33.043
Hey, Jim.
We're just talking shop.

01:33.078 --> 01:34.545
Wouldn't want to waste
your time.

01:34.580 --> 01:37.214
Don't mind me. Just minding
my own business here.

01:37.249 --> 01:38.549
Mind if I take notes on it?

01:38.584 --> 01:40.050
Just kiddin'.
[ Laughs ]

01:40.085 --> 01:41.051
[ Alarm ringing ]
- Wha?

01:41.086 --> 01:42.319
It's a fire!

01:42.354 --> 01:43.654
[ Ringing continues ]

01:43.689 --> 01:45.122
Those darn kids
pullin' the fire alarm!

01:45.157 --> 01:46.423
We got to save the kids!

01:46.458 --> 01:47.758
Jim, it's just
a false alarm!

01:47.793 --> 01:48.826
Fire! Everyone out!

01:48.861 --> 01:49.894
Fire!!
-Fire?

01:49.929 --> 01:51.495
-Fire!
-Fire?

01:51.530 --> 01:52.897
Fire!!

01:52.932 --> 01:54.565
-Fire!
-Fire!

01:54.600 --> 01:56.167
Everyone out!
Let's go!

01:56.202 --> 01:57.968
H'okay, let's go.

01:58.003 --> 01:59.603
[ Humming ]

01:59.638 --> 02:02.740
-Why are we still out here?
-Okay, all accounted for.

02:02.775 --> 02:04.775
Okay, back to class,
everyone!

02:04.810 --> 02:06.076
I know that was exciting

02:06.111 --> 02:08.245
but please,
quiet in the halls, okay?

02:08.280 --> 02:09.747
Yep, you kids better shape up

02:09.782 --> 02:11.682
or else we're going to have to
call the cops on you.

02:11.717 --> 02:14.418
[ Chuckles ]
[ Siren wails ]

02:14.453 --> 02:15.953
Oh, great, she's here!

02:15.988 --> 02:18.455
Oh, uh, I mean, Melanie,
I-I was just kiddin'.

02:18.490 --> 02:20.758
Officer, thank you so much again
for coming.

02:20.793 --> 02:22.259
Serve and protect.
That's the oath.

02:22.294 --> 02:23.761
[ Crack! ]
- [ Groans ]

02:23.796 --> 02:24.795
Ca-Carol?

02:24.830 --> 02:25.629
Carol!

02:25.664 --> 02:28.299
[ Militaristic music plays ]

02:28.334 --> 02:30.768
Uh, wait, you two
know each other?

02:30.803 --> 02:32.269
So great to see ya.

02:32.304 --> 02:34.605
You look fit.
H-How long's it been?

02:34.640 --> 02:35.940
What are you
doing here, Jim?

02:35.975 --> 02:38.209
Yeah, what<i> are</i> we
doing here, Reese?

02:38.244 --> 02:39.944
This is dumb.
I'm going inside.

02:39.979 --> 02:42.646
Hey, Noles! I didn't say
it's safe to go back in.

02:42.681 --> 02:45.883
Get back here!
Noles! Garf! Noles!!

02:45.918 --> 02:49.453
Ha-ha. Some kinds are
very independent. Heh.

02:49.488 --> 02:51.121
Anyway, I work here as a...

02:51.156 --> 02:53.557
Well, I like to think of myself
as a school disciplinarian.

02:53.592 --> 02:54.959
[ Chuckles nervously ]

02:54.994 --> 02:56.627
Almost a...like a vice
principal, but, uh --

02:56.662 --> 02:59.730
Um, excuse me.
Can I touch your gun?

02:59.765 --> 03:04.735
Okay, everyone, say hello to
our new friend, Officer Moody.

03:04.770 --> 03:07.338
Students:
Hi, Officer Moody.

03:07.373 --> 03:09.506
Excuse me, ma'am.
Do you carry a gun?

03:09.541 --> 03:11.475
[ Stammers ]
Yes, I am a police officer,

03:11.510 --> 03:13.544
and I carry a weapon
to protect the public.

03:13.579 --> 03:17.481
Anything else related to the gun
will<i> not</i> be addressed.

03:17.516 --> 03:19.483
Do you have a gun?

03:19.518 --> 03:22.019
[ Students snickering ]

03:22.054 --> 03:24.221
What?
I wanna know.

03:24.256 --> 03:27.658
Okay, so your teacher tells me
this class has had some problems

03:27.693 --> 03:29.493
following
the rules recently,

03:29.528 --> 03:31.862
specifically with some
fire-alarm pranksters.

03:31.897 --> 03:35.332
Now, why do you think we have
fire alarms in schools?

03:35.367 --> 03:37.167
So we can get out of class.

03:37.202 --> 03:38.402
[ Laughter ]

03:38.437 --> 03:40.437
Oh, so you think safety
is a joke.

03:40.472 --> 03:41.772
No, no, that's fine.

03:41.807 --> 03:43.540
We'll come back to
the fire alarm later.

03:43.575 --> 03:46.076
Let's say it's the morning
and you are playing outside.

03:46.111 --> 03:49.179
A stranger comes up to you
and says, "Hey, I know your mom.

03:49.214 --> 03:50.848
Let me give you a ride
to school."

03:50.883 --> 03:53.350
Oh, oh, oh!
Um, you say, "Yes.

03:53.385 --> 03:54.451
Thank you."

03:54.486 --> 03:55.853
[ Laughter ]

03:55.888 --> 03:59.356
Wrong! You never get in the car
with a stranger!

03:59.391 --> 04:02.693
But...you said
that they know my mom.

04:02.728 --> 04:05.429
Oh, he's got you there.
They do know his mom.

04:05.464 --> 04:07.264
-Right?
-No, Clarence,

04:07.299 --> 04:08.432
you should really
never get in the car

04:08.467 --> 04:09.366
with someone you don't know.

04:09.401 --> 04:10.467
Yeah, well,

04:10.502 --> 04:11.735
I might not carry
a big gun,

04:11.770 --> 04:13.203
but I know a thing or two
about safety.

04:13.238 --> 04:15.239
After all, me and Moody
go way back, and, yeah.

04:15.274 --> 04:17.474
[ Growls ]
- Used to be partners.

04:17.509 --> 04:18.976
-What?
-Are you for real?

04:19.011 --> 04:21.378
And if there's one thing
I learned about safety...

04:21.413 --> 04:23.614
You know, actually,
I think Officer Moody

04:23.649 --> 04:25.950
has prepared a presentation
for us, uh,

04:25.985 --> 04:27.418
so let's, uh, do that.

04:31.423 --> 04:33.057
[ Gurgling ]

04:33.092 --> 04:34.291
That is what happens

04:34.326 --> 04:36.126
when you get in the car
with a stranger.

04:36.161 --> 04:37.761
[ Slurps ]

04:37.796 --> 04:39.830
-Thank you, Chelsea.
-Mm-hmm.

04:39.865 --> 04:41.732
Now, I am going
to demonstrate

04:41.767 --> 04:43.767
the proper way
to escape capture.

04:43.802 --> 04:46.070
Little boy,
restrain me with this.

04:46.105 --> 04:48.906
Are you gonna arrest me?

04:48.941 --> 04:50.174
No.

04:50.209 --> 04:51.775
Bunny ears
go through the...

04:51.810 --> 04:54.345
around the tree
- and through the loop and --

04:54.380 --> 04:56.413
That's all.
Thank you.

04:56.448 --> 04:57.848
You're welcome!

04:57.883 --> 05:00.751
Freeing myself
may seem impossible,

05:00.786 --> 05:02.920
but if you know
the right maneuver...

05:02.955 --> 05:05.089
[ Groans ]

05:05.124 --> 05:06.924
-Whoa.
-Whew!

05:06.959 --> 05:08.859
[ Glass shatters ] That's
a pretty solid technique.

05:08.894 --> 05:10.594
Excuse me.

05:10.629 --> 05:12.596
But I actually know a more
effective method.

05:12.631 --> 05:16.100
Officer Moody,
if you would.

05:16.135 --> 05:18.002
[ Laughs ]
Right.

05:18.037 --> 05:19.970
We need a volunteer.

05:20.005 --> 05:21.839
Uh, come here, Melanie.

05:21.874 --> 05:23.340
Yeah, o-okay.

05:23.375 --> 05:25.309
Agh, yeah.
Nice and tight.

05:25.344 --> 05:26.443
Oh!

05:26.478 --> 05:27.711
Okay, I'm done.

05:27.746 --> 05:30.481
Now, so you see,
it's all about the hips.

05:30.516 --> 05:33.617
[ Grunting ]

05:33.652 --> 05:36.453
This...son of --
-Jim!

05:36.488 --> 05:38.155
[ Whispering ] You're
embarrassing yourself.

05:38.190 --> 05:40.124
[ Normal voice ]
Okay, let's move out, everyone!

05:40.159 --> 05:42.493
Next, I'm going to demonstrate
the proper use of a taser.

05:42.528 --> 05:45.662
Belson:
- Okay, now I'm interested.

05:45.697 --> 05:49.299
I almost got it.
You, uh [grunts]

05:49.334 --> 05:51.635
I might be able
to break it.

05:51.670 --> 05:53.137
With my teeth.

05:53.172 --> 05:57.374
Oh, Clarence.
- I was a cop for two years.

05:57.409 --> 06:00.878
Beloved, feared,
respected.

06:02.347 --> 06:04.081
[ Humming ]

06:04.116 --> 06:05.883
Moody.
-Huh?

06:05.918 --> 06:08.752
You ever heard of
the donut pancake?

06:08.787 --> 06:10.588
Hoo-ah!

06:15.761 --> 06:20.230
Mm? Donut pancake!
Donut pancake!

06:20.265 --> 06:21.899
[ Choking ]

06:21.934 --> 06:23.734
[ Vomiting ]
- Tuh.

06:23.769 --> 06:26.270
Moody and I were like
the eyes of a tiger.

06:26.305 --> 06:28.472
No one wanted to mess with us.

06:29.808 --> 06:31.341
Go these babies from the web.

06:31.376 --> 06:33.110
[ Twinkle! ]
Free delivery.

06:33.145 --> 06:35.512
Hee-ah!
-[ Grunts ]

06:35.547 --> 06:37.014
Everything was going great,

06:37.049 --> 06:39.016
until that one fateful
assignment

06:39.051 --> 06:39.850
that would be my last.

06:39.885 --> 06:41.351
Oh, look at the monkey go!

06:41.386 --> 06:42.853
Get the banana! [ Laughs ]

06:42.888 --> 06:45.422
The grand opening of a new
children's library.

06:45.457 --> 06:49.193
Moody and I were called in to
help the mayor at the ceremony.

06:49.228 --> 06:50.694
I was running a bit late.

06:50.729 --> 06:52.529
Must have taken
a wrong turn somehow,

06:52.564 --> 06:54.531
'cause next thing you know...

06:54.566 --> 06:55.566
[ Both scream ]

06:55.601 --> 06:57.468
[ Screaming ]

06:57.503 --> 06:59.837
[ Siren wails ]

07:01.473 --> 07:04.141
Aaaah!

07:04.176 --> 07:05.542
[ Whimpers ]

07:05.577 --> 07:06.710
[ Grunts ]

07:06.745 --> 07:09.646
That was the end
of my police career.

07:09.681 --> 07:11.982
[ Laughter ]

07:13.585 --> 07:15.820
[ Humming ]

07:17.623 --> 07:21.225
Oh, wow. You were a real-life
cop back then.

07:21.260 --> 07:22.659
[ Groans ]

07:22.694 --> 07:25.596
[ Straining ] You must've felt
like a real hero.

07:25.631 --> 07:27.064
I'm no hero.

07:27.099 --> 07:28.232
[ Thud! ]

07:28.267 --> 07:30.100
I'm just a saggy joke.

07:30.135 --> 07:32.136
No runnin' with scissors!

07:33.639 --> 07:35.606
Ah, what am I saying?

07:37.176 --> 07:40.177
Thanks, Clarence.
- You would've made a good cop.

07:40.212 --> 07:41.512
Whoa, really?

07:41.547 --> 07:44.248
Does that mean I get my own
very own binoculars?

07:44.283 --> 07:46.083
Aw.

07:46.118 --> 07:47.918
No one respects me here.

07:47.953 --> 07:50.354
It's time I leave
Aberdale Elementary.

07:50.389 --> 07:51.922
I'll take those.

07:51.957 --> 07:53.957
Wait.
You can't quit.

07:53.992 --> 07:56.493
Who's gonna tell me
not to slouch?

07:56.528 --> 07:58.028
You can slouch, Clarence.

07:58.063 --> 07:59.596
Aw.

07:59.631 --> 08:01.498
So long, detention room.

08:01.533 --> 08:03.634
[ Sobbing ]
You served me well.

08:06.305 --> 08:08.438
[ Laughs evilly ]

08:08.473 --> 08:10.807
[ Alarm ringing ]
Come on, Mr. Reese.

08:10.842 --> 08:12.776
Who's gonna drink
all the coffee a--

08:12.811 --> 08:14.044
Hmm?

08:14.079 --> 08:14.878
Fire!?

08:14.913 --> 08:16.213
-There's a fire!
-Ah!

08:16.248 --> 08:18.448
Fire!
-Oh-ah!!

08:18.483 --> 08:20.117
Fire, fire!

08:20.152 --> 08:21.618
One last ride!
Everyone out!

08:21.653 --> 08:23.453
-Fire! Fire!
-Hustle! Hustle!

08:23.488 --> 08:24.688
Let's go!
-Oh.

08:24.723 --> 08:27.124
It's just Belson.
-Belson Noles!

08:27.159 --> 08:28.692
Oh, you're in big trouble,
Mister.

08:28.727 --> 08:30.360
Yeah, yeah, just give me
a detention or whatever.

08:30.395 --> 08:32.796
[ Thud! ] - And where do
you think you're going?

08:32.831 --> 08:35.632
Are you aware pulling
the fire alarm is a felony?

08:35.667 --> 08:37.467
[ Stammers ]
Wh-wh-what?

08:37.502 --> 08:39.136
Uh, Moody, he's just
a child.

08:39.171 --> 08:41.471
I-It was just a prank!
It was a joke!

08:41.506 --> 08:42.873
What's going on here?

08:42.908 --> 08:45.309
Resisting an officer will add
to your sentence!

08:45.344 --> 08:46.376
Excuse me. Uh...

08:46.411 --> 08:48.312
-[ Growls ]
-Oh, my!

08:48.347 --> 08:49.546
Wow. Heh.

08:49.581 --> 08:50.814
Everything is
a big joke, huh?

08:50.849 --> 08:54.484
You're going away
for a<i> long</i> time.

08:54.519 --> 08:57.588
-Handcuffs.
-[ Wails ]

08:57.623 --> 08:59.690
[ Sobbing ]

08:59.725 --> 09:02.126
But, Mi-Mister Reese,
please!

09:03.562 --> 09:05.395
Wait.

09:05.430 --> 09:07.364
<i>I</i> pulled the alarm.

09:07.399 --> 09:08.732
[ Kids gasping ]

09:08.767 --> 09:10.767
Go on now, cuff me.

09:10.802 --> 09:13.770
You haven't changed a bit.

09:13.805 --> 09:15.672
You have the right
to remain silent.

09:15.707 --> 09:17.074
Anything you say
can and will be used

09:17.109 --> 09:18.675
against you
in a court of law.

09:18.710 --> 09:19.876
Oh, no, wait, wait.
Come on, now.

09:19.911 --> 09:21.111
Is this part of
the demonstration?

09:21.146 --> 09:23.046
-I don't think so.
-Wait!

09:23.081 --> 09:25.916
I did the thing!
It was me!

09:25.951 --> 09:28.552
Pulled it with my naughty
little ol' hand.

09:28.587 --> 09:30.220
He's lying.
<i>I</i> did it.

09:30.255 --> 09:32.389
No, wait,<i> I</i> pulled
the alarm first!

09:32.424 --> 09:34.224
Can you arrest me first?

09:34.259 --> 09:35.926
I'm a menace.

09:35.961 --> 09:37.427
No.
No, I didn't do it.

09:37.462 --> 09:40.030
But I saw Mavis
pulling it.

09:40.065 --> 09:41.965
-I did it!
-It was me!

09:42.000 --> 09:43.433
[ Kids clamoring ]
[ Gulps ]

09:43.468 --> 09:45.769
You can't arrest
all of us.

09:45.804 --> 09:48.105
[ Kids gasping ]

09:48.140 --> 09:52.476
Man:<i> Uh, any available officer,</i>
<i>A-114 is on fire.</i>

09:52.511 --> 09:54.211
<i>Repeat! My car is on fire!!</i>

09:54.246 --> 09:56.313
Don't you have a big important
job to do?

09:56.348 --> 09:59.616
You'll never change.
Get out of my way, Jim!

09:59.651 --> 10:01.084
This is Officer Moody.
I'm on it!

10:01.119 --> 10:03.053
Mr. Reese!
Mr. Reese!

10:03.088 --> 10:05.255
Don't stand up
too quickly or...

10:05.290 --> 10:07.057
Oh.

10:07.092 --> 10:08.925
Jim, your, uh --
the handcuffs.

10:08.960 --> 10:10.827
Your -- Your butt.
They're crushed!

10:10.862 --> 10:13.096
You used your butt
to escape the law.

10:13.131 --> 10:15.465
[ Kids murmuring excitedly ]

10:15.500 --> 10:17.134
You mean<i> this</i> ol' thing?

10:17.169 --> 10:20.504
I was known for my excessive
butt force back at the station.

10:20.539 --> 10:22.273
[ Laughter ]

10:23.642 --> 10:25.075
[ Slurping ]

10:25.110 --> 10:27.477
Hey, Chelsea,
you better slow down.

10:27.512 --> 10:28.512
Or else...

10:28.547 --> 10:29.646
Whoo-pa!

10:29.681 --> 10:30.747
Hmm-hmm.

10:30.782 --> 10:32.149
Hut, two, three, four.

10:32.184 --> 10:34.985
Hey, you two are gonna be
late for class.

10:35.020 --> 10:37.621
Don't make me use my police
"buttality" on you two.

10:37.656 --> 10:40.123
[ Both laugh ]

10:40.158 --> 10:42.025
Clarence, what did I tell you
about slouchin'?

10:42.060 --> 10:44.294
Look at that!
-Yes, sir!

10:44.329 --> 10:47.164
Belson!
Spit out that gum, boy!

10:48.633 --> 10:50.034
Hmm?

10:51.703 --> 10:53.370
Pbht!

10:53.405 --> 10:55.772
This may look like a chewed-up
piece of gum,

10:55.807 --> 10:58.975
but this right here,
this is progress.

10:59.010 --> 11:02.246
Wow, Mr. Reese.
You touched someone's gum.

11:04.916 --> 11:06.283
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:07.853 --> 11:10.154
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:11.690 --> 11:13.724
♪ Picking my nose ♪
